One killed, nine injured following a collision between a taxi and a truck on the R102 road near Inanda Verulam Durban on Monday .It is believed that the truck sideswiped the taxi then veered off the road and overturned.On arrival paramedics found crumpled remains of the taxi on the roadway with some of the injured still trapped.Jaws of Life were used to free the injured while medics worked tirelessly to stabilise the patients.A female patient that was airlifted to hospital died soon after arriving at the hospital due to the extensive injuries that she sustained.Arrive alive has urged motorist to be cautious during the festive season.TNA Reporter